Maven Lifecycle
What is Maven Lifecycle?

In Apache Maven, a lifecycle is a sequence of phases used to build and manage a project.

It defines:

How a project is 
built
Tested
Packaged
Installed
Deployed

Maven automates the complete build process using predefined lifecycle phases.

Why Maven Lifecycle is Important

The Maven lifecycle helps:

Standardize project builds
Automate repetitive tasks
Reduce manual work
Ensure consistency across projects
Integrate easily with CI/CD tools
Maven has 3 Built-in Lifecycles
Lifecycle	Purpose
Default	Handles project build and deployment
Clean	Removes previous build files
Site	Generates project documentation
1. Default Lifecycle

This is the main lifecycle used in most Maven projects.

It handles:

Compilation
Testing
Packaging
Installation
Deployment
Important Phases of Default Lifecycle
Phase	Description
validate	Validates project structure and pom.xml
compile	Compiles source code
test	Runs unit tests
package	Creates JAR/WAR
verify	Runs quality checks
install	Installs artifact into local repository
deploy	Deploys artifact to remote repository


Lifecycle Flow
validate
   ↓
compile
   ↓
test
   ↓
package
   ↓
verify
   ↓
install
   ↓
deploy


Example Commands
Compile Project
mvn compile
Compiles source code
Generates .class files
Run Tests
mvn test
Executes unit tests
Uses Surefire plugin
Package Application
mvn package
Creates JAR or WAR file
Output stored in target/
Install into Local Repository
mvn install
Stores artifact in local Maven repository
Local repository location:
~/.m2/repository
Deploy to Remote Repository
mvn deploy
Uploads artifact to remote repository like Nexus or Artifactory
Important Concept

When a phase is executed, all previous phases execute automatically.

Example:

mvn package

Automatically runs:

validate
compile
test
package
2. Clean Lifecycle

Used to remove old build files.

Important Phase
Phase	Description
clean	Deletes target directory

Command:

mvn clean
Clean Lifecycle Flow
clean
3. Site Lifecycle

Used to generate project reports and documentation.

Important Phases
Phase	Description
site	Generates project site
site-deploy	Deploys generated site

Command:

mvn site
Maven Lifecycle and Plugins

Each lifecycle phase is linked to plugin goals.

Lifecycle Phase	Plugin Goal
compile	compiler:compile
test	surefire:test
package	jar:jar
install	install:install
deploy	deploy:deploy
Real-Time Example

Suppose you build a Spring Boot application.

Command:

mvn clean install

What happens:

Old target folder removed
Source code compiled
Unit tests executed
JAR file created
Artifact stored in local repository
